# Narrow Highway — Caddy reverse proxy (auto-TLS via Let's Encrypt).
# Two faces, one engine: .com is the secular reach, .org is the witness.
#
# CURRENT LIVE REALITY (2026-06-28): narrowhighway.com is served by 1.0 (the `nh-engine`
# service) on :8000. The `nh-com.service` (2.0 secular) in this directory is PREPARED but
# NOT enabled — the .com cutover is gated on 2.0 reaching feature parity with 1.0 (the keep,
# library, workspace, etc.). So the .com block below points at :8000 = whatever runs there
# (currently 1.0). narrowhighway.org IS 2.0 — the witness face (`nh-org` on :8001).
#
# `header_up X-Forwarded-For {remote_host}` OVERRIDES any client-sent value — defense-in-depth
# for the operator keep gate (which also ignores X-Forwarded-For in code; see web/keep.py).

narrowhighway.com, www.narrowhighway.com {
	encode gzip
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8000 {
		header_up X-Forwarded-For {remote_host}
	}
}

narrowhighway.org, www.narrowhighway.org {
	encode gzip
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8001 {
		header_up X-Forwarded-For {remote_host}
	}
}
